
[1]amaranthus

   AMARANTH'US, n. [Gr.of a neg. and to decay; so called, it is said,
   because, when cropped, it does not soon wither.]

   Flower-gentle; a genus of plants, of many species. Of these the
   tricolored has long been cultivated in gardens, on account of the
   beauty of its variegated leaves.
